HEADWORD: Mascled
<hw>Mas"cled</hw> <pr>(-k'ld)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Composed of, or
covered with, lozenge-shaped scales; having lozenge-shaped
divisions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mascled armor</b></col>, <cd>armor composed of small
lozenge-shaped scales of metal fastened on a foundation of leather or
quilted cloth.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

